Additional information

Comparing iShares ETFs to other leading ETFs

iShares is a market leader in the management and development of ETFs.* iShares is well known by institutional and retail investors for having some of the most liquid and largest ETFs available. You can easily compare iShares ETFs and other ETFs offered by Fidelity in our ETF Research Center.

The commission-free purchases on the 70 iShares ETFs must be done online at Fidelity.com, Active Trader Pro®, Wealth-Lab Pro®, or through Fidelity's wireless channels.

Note: A short-term trading fee of $4.95 will be charged for any sales that occur within 30 days of the original purchase of the ETF with the oldest shares in the account being depleted first. The fee for shares sold on FAST, Fidelity's automated phone system, within 30 days of purchase is $12.95.

All iShares ETFs are not margin-eligible for 30 days from settlement, similar to mutual funds. For margin customers, positions will automatically become margin eligible in their account after 30 days from settlement.

Options on any iShares ETF products are not commission-free.
